      "markdown": "# üîÆ B11 ‚Äî Futuro & Condicional + ir a + infinitivo (B1)\n\n**Goal:** Express future plans and hypothetical situations.**\n\n---\n\n## üìå Futuro simple\n- Add endings to the infinitive: **-√©, -√°s, -√°, -emos, -√©is, -√°n**\n- Same endings for -ar/-er/-ir\n\n**Examples:**\n- *Ma√±ana estudiar√©.* ‚Äî I will study tomorrow\n- *Viajaremos a Madrid.* ‚Äî We will travel to Madrid\n\n**Irregular stems:**\n- tener ‚Üí tendr-, salir ‚Üí saldr-, venir ‚Üí vendr-, poder ‚Üí podr-, poner ‚Üí pondr-, decir ‚Üí dir-, hacer ‚Üí har-, querer ‚Üí querr-, saber ‚Üí sabr-\n\n---\n\n## üìå Condicional simple\n- Add endings to infinitive: **-√≠a, -√≠as, -√≠a, -√≠amos, -√≠ais, -√≠an**\n\n**Examples:**\n- *Viajar√≠a a Jap√≥n si tuviera dinero.* ‚Äî I would travel to Japan if I had money\n- *¬øQu√© har√≠as t√∫?* ‚Äî What would you do?\n\n**Uses:** polite requests, hypothetical actions, reported speech\n\n---\n\n## ‚ö° Ir a + infinitivo\n- Used for **near future plans**\n- conjugate **ir** in present + **a + infinitive**\n\n**Examples:**\n- *Voy a estudiar ahora.* ‚Äî I‚Äôm going to study now\n- *Vamos a salir.* ‚Äî We are going to go out\n\n---\n\n> üìù Summary:  \n> **futuro = will**, **condicional = would**, **ir a + inf = going to (near future)**\n",
      "references": []
    }
